Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
timing_enable...e_clock_gating(25.10)    timing_enable...e_clock_gating(25.10)

Name
       timing_enable_tristate_clock_gating

Syntax
       timing_enable_tristate_clock_gating

       {true | false}

       Default: false

       The  timing system infers gated-clock checks in the design where a data
       and clock path intersect at a combinational device. When this global is
       set to true, inferred gated-clock checks are added when clock and  data
       signals converge through the tristate enable and data input of tristate
       buffers.  By  default  (a setting of false), gated-clock checks are not
       added for these situations.

       To set this global variable, use the set_global command.

